Text.Value: Excuse me? These are the only games worth playing.
I'm breaking up with you.
Then we'll do it tonight. And come the morning, we will be together forever.
Really? Because Shadowheart has the ear of a literal god.
Goodbye, darling. And good luck.

EditorData.NodeContext: [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player. Make it count :P]

Text.Value: And I intend to. I can go anywhere, do anything, indulge in whatever hedonism or carnage I like. Once I stay out of the sun.
You can't want to die like this, Karlach. Not when you could still go back to the Hells. Not when you could still live.
Let's put our enemies to the sword!
Well. That's that, then.

EditorData.NodeContext: Accepting bad news

Text.Value: I can't say what the future holds for us, but I know we'll be facing it together.
I'll never forget you. I'll never forget what you did for this world.
I want to sit on your lap, sipping blood from a chalice, ruling the Gate from our foul throne.
We'll start with Baldur's Gate - Let's make this city ours.
Anyway, taking power in this city will need to be a subtle process. We wouldn't want to spook the cattle, after all.
And you've changed too, of course. A... different aesthetic, but with such power.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'different' - player is a mind flayer now. Astarion's not impressed with the look, but is very hungry for their power

Text.Value: It certainly is when you're around.
It is a pity, we were rather good together. I'll never forget it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bittersweet

Text.Value: I would understand if you wanted to go your own way.
Is that what you want? Is this what you want?

EditorData.NodeContext: "This" referring to "us being in a relationship". Maybe with a "you and me" hand gesture.

Text.Value: True, it's a vast world out there; there are plenty of places to hide.
And I'm sure trouble would find us sooner or later. It always seems to.
I don't think so. I have my own plans.
It is a shame, though. You were something special.
I don't need you - I don't need anyone. I already have everything I want.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hiding his anger now

Text.Value: Then you shall. We'll travel the lands together, tasting everything Faer√ªn has to offer.
It would never work, sweetie. Not when I look like this and you... well, you're monstrous.
After all, you helped me attain perfection. I owe all of this to you, so... thank you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coming off all sincere

Text.Value: Eh, let's see what happens. Life is a big adventure.
And neither would I. Together, we can do anything.
We've dealt with the parasite. And you dealt with Cazador. I'll never be in someone's power again.

EditorData.logicalname: ASTARION NOT PRESENT DEATH OF CAZADOR

Text.Value: Now the blood-whispers are gone from me, I just want to settle down quietly for a while.
Let's settle down somewhere and enjoy the peace.
Actually, I will go and do my own thing.
It's too soon - we need more time together. You need to live your life, damn it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realising Karlach is going to die, not really accepting it.

Text.Value: So, Karlach... What do you say?
The Absolute may be gone, but others will rise against us. Maybe even our old allies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reflective on the last line

Text.Value: Who knows - perhaps we've only just begun.
My sweet, I thought you'd never ask.
Maybe it's better if we part.
Being free to choose love, choose a new family - that is my own way.
I am no longer your spawn. I will choose my own path.
I will see you again, my love. I'm not sure how, but if I know anything, it's that death isn't always the end.
True, if we can kill a Netherbrain, we can kill anything.
A shame. I was looking forward to having you as my consort. But we can still be powerful allies.
You - what? I didn't think you'd actually agree!
Astarion. No.
I just can't, Astarion. I'd rather die here, in my home, than try to survive the Hells. I just want to see the sky one last time.
But fine. You don't need my friendship and I don't need you sliming around my palace.
No - I swore I'd never go back, and I meant it. I just want to see the sky one last time.
The people may not appreciate you now that you're a grotesque freak, but I do.
I'll help you find a way to walk in the sun again.
But if you won't accept my kindness, that's on your slimy head.
Like I'm going to blow at any minute.
I see what's happening, Karlach. The end is coming. But it doesn't have to look like this.
I don't know - Wyll's a Grand Duke. That's pretty powerful...
Then what are we waiting for, darling?
And Zariel will be far too busy with Raphael to worry about scouring the plane for you.
And what you did for me.
Let's see everything, now I'm free of my Father! I want to travel the world.
I want to see the world, with you at my side.
I just need to be sure - is this what you want? I mean... this.

EditorData.NodeContext: "This" referring to "us being in a relationship". Maybe with a "you and me" hand gesture.

Text.Value: I will miss you, though. Since the moment we met, you have been spectacular.
Exactly my thought! Together, we can rule this city, and the cattle won't even realise it's happening.
I can make my own way in the world. There's enough of it out there.
And if there's a chance, no matter how small, I'm going to take it.
We have a beautiful, bloody future to look forward to, my love. I can't be sure what it holds for us, but I know one thing.
I want to live forever. Make me a vampire.
And you promise you'll make me a full vampire soon?
I am, but I'm more than that. I have evolved beyond the person I was.
Perhaps we'll even meet again someday. The future is yet to be written, after all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not a threat, but not NOT a threat

Text.Value: Can't we enjoy ourselves for one day before worrying about the next threat?
I shed that person when I shed their skin.
It feels so good. Freedom - true freedom. Finally.
Of course, I'm still me!
A pity, because we were rather excellent together. A love for the ages...
Why not? Life wouldn't taste half as sweet without you by my side.
It's more of a gamble without the tadpoles, but maybe you're right. The best defence is a timely murder...
I mean it, this is what I want. And it's the smart move.
Excuse me? What plans? Lurking in the sewers, feasting on rat brains?
And it's such a pity, because you were beautiful. You would have looked magnificent ruling by my side.

EditorData.NodeContext: emphasise 'beautiful'

Text.Value: It is indeed. We can travel the lands together, tasting everything Faer√ªn has to offer.
How neither one of us is free. How Cazador's still out there, and you're-...
This is going to be fun.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a wicked smile [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player. Make it count :P]

Text.Value: Perhaps we'll adjust, perhaps we won't, but you mean too much for me to walk away.
I understand - I want this.
True, if he ever branches out from fighting the Infernal, he'd be a formidable threat.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contemplating

Text.Value: And that makes us the most powerful couple in the world.

EditorData.NodeContext: stress on 'us'

Text.Value: How I'm free of Cazador. How I have a whole new life stretching out in front of me, and you... you won't be able to join me, will you?

EditorData.logicalname: KARLACH GOING TO HELLS - CAZADOR DEAD

Text.Value: So I was thinking; where can I go that is devoid of sunlight, filled with violence, and has the one person I want to spend all my time with?
But even if we can't, I'll never forget the person you were. I'll never forget what you did for this world.
Well, what are you? Is the person I loved still in there?
Plus, Cazador could search for a thousand years and never find me there.
Don't threaten me with a good time, darling.
I want to break up with you.
And now I can see it all. At night, obviously.
And it would mean setting off on another adventure together.
Really? And what does your path include? Lurking in the sewers, feasting on rat brains?
We can start slowly - quietly charming and manipulating key figures, building up our network of puppets.
True, he has a lot of power at his fingertips. He could be a threat.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contemplating

Text.Value: You'd discard me, just like that?
How dare you! After all I've done for you - after everything I've sacrificed!
Maybe, but life is what you make it. And I want to make mine with you.
But until the moment's right, we can still be together. We can still taste all the delights of this world.
When the time comes, we'll kill him together.
Not least of whom is our friend, the new Grand Duke.
Let's raze the Hells.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a wicked smile

Text.Value: Well of course I don't want to. But if they get in my way...

EditorData.NodeContext: "of course I don't WANT to kill our friends. But..."

Text.Value: And we're going to have a lot of fun.

EditorData.NodeContext: [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player. Make it count :P]

Text.Value: I'll find some nice, dark place where neither you nor Cazador will ever bother me again.
I don't know - Wyll's the Blade of Avernus. Pretty powerful...
You - what? Now? After all this?!
Before long we'll have our hands on every string in this city, and they will dance however we tell them to.
Hello darling.
We may need a purge or two. Just to secure our position.
No, this is what I want.
You could make me a vampire. Then we'd be even stronger together.
A pity you won't be here to see it.
So let's put our new-found power to use.
I'll never forget the person you used to be - the beauty I bedded, the warrior I fought beside, the hero that saved this city.
We are rather excellent together, you know. And united, there is nothing we can't do.
Thank you, my love. Thank you.

EditorData.NodeContext: [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player. Make it count :P]

Text.Value: You stupid, ungrateful, little- Fine. Fine! To hells with you, I'll take Baldur's Gate myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Manages to rein in his rage, but is still very tense

Text.Value: I can feel my strength growing. Every day that passes, I gain new abilities.
Allies? I thought we were friends. More than friends, even.
Oh, I've heard. But isn't that part of the fun? Bringing chaos to a whole new realm?
I can build up my power here in the light, while you lurk below in the shadows.
Are you sure about this? The Hells are a horrific place.
Yes, I do.
All right. If that's what you want, then - then I'll be here with you. No matter what comes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Just heard that his love is determined to let herself die, rather than fighting on in Hell

Text.Value: No, I think you're right. It's probably best to leave things here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Accepting a breakup

Text.Value: Now get the hells out of my city.

EditorData.NodeContext: [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player]

Text.Value: No, a simple alliance is far more useful to us both.
Concentrate. You can barely hear him through the blaze of chaos threatening to explode from within.
Maybe we could make a difference out there. Although, I do need to ask...
I'm glad. Although I'm not sure what the expectations are around... us?

EditorData.NodeContext: Genuinely glad. 'us' referring to your relationship together.

Text.Value: I don't know, it is a big change. And as much as I care for you... I don't know.
I wish you well out there. Just don't come knocking on my door - I'll have a lot of hungry mouths to feed.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little bitter, but more a warning than a threat

Text.Value: I swore I'd never go back. I haven't changed my mind.
And if we did it together - if I came with you - who knows what we'd achieve?
But you won't get rid of me so easily, my love. Death isn't always the end of life - that much I know for certain.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still processing his love's impending death

Text.Value: You know, now that our enemies have fallen, I might be the most powerful person in the world.
Say nothing. Concentrate on keeping the inferno inside you from boiling over.
Why wait? Let's go kill him.
Yes, I can work below the surface - you can work above.
As for you... I wish you well. I'm sure you'll land on your feet.

EditorData.NodeContext: trying to get on the high horse

Text.Value: My love. You always know the right thing to say.
Yes. We will be powerful allies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Astarion's taking the player in, liking the potential in them

Text.Value: I'm offering you a chance to be useful - to be more than the monster you've become. I thought you'd be grateful.
It isn't fair. It just... is what it is.
This would be different, Karlach. Together, we can face anything - no matter what Avernus throws at us.
How neither one of us is free. How Cazador's still out there - how you're... you're coming to the end, aren't you?

EditorData.logicalname: KARLACH GOING TO HELLS - CAZADOR ALIVE

Text.Value: We will need to be careful, of course. There are still powerful forces in the city.
I wouldn't want it any other way.
We should find the vampire spawn in the Underdark. They'll need guidance.
But fine. If that's what you want, so be it.
But just because you're a monster, it doesn't mean we don't have a glorious future ahead of us.
The tadpole is gone, which means your future is mine to decide.
Think about it: in the Hells I never have to fear the sun, I can kill anyone I want, and I'll be with you.
My darling, of course! I want nothing more.

EditorData.NodeContext: overly sincere - he doesn't really mean it

Text.Value: Haha! Oh darling, please. I can't have something like this as my lover. The mechanics alone...
Are you sure you want to do this, though? I mean... this?

EditorData.NodeContext: "This" referring to "us being in a relationship". Maybe with a "you and me" hand gesture.

Text.Value: Oh, darling. I love the way you think.
I might be free of the parasite, but Cazador's still out there. Without the tadpole's protection, he just has to find me to claim me.
Very well, then. Die if you want to, I will carry on regardless.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little aloof, but not angry or cruel

Text.Value: I see. And how does this newly-evolved version of you feel about me?
My love, stuck with this ticking time bomb in your chest. It's nothing short of a tragedy.
There are thousands of vampire spawn in the Underdark, just waiting for a leader. I'll find them.
Let's leave Baldur's Gate. He can't control you if he can't find you.
It's a huge world out there that this washed-up Bhaal cultist has never seen. Won't you take me?
Why not go somewhere new? It's a big world out there.
There's no backing out now - we'll be together forever. I can promise you that.
This isn't what you want yet. I'm sure you'll come around in your own good time.
True, we could help each other.
So. What happens next?

EditorData.NodeContext: composing himself, moving on

Text.Value: Then you'd better live that new life of yours to the fullest. Live enough for both of us.
Do you still want to be together?
So would I. And I hope we can find some place for love in our new - whatever this is.
We make a good team - let's go be heroes together.
True, the spawn will need someone to lead them. Otherwise they'll just be a murderous, blood-sucking horde.
Excuse me? You want to leave - now? At my moment of triumph? Have you lost your mind?!

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to grasp what's just been said

Text.Value: We are rather good together, aren't we? I never saw myself as a hero, but fighting alongside you has been special.
After all, Raphael's gone to wage war against Zariel. She'll be too busy fighting him to come after you.
How I'm free of the parasite - free of Cazador. How I'll never be in someone's power again.
Of course, you will be a spawn before you can become a true vampire, but that's a small detail.
It isn't fair. Not after everything we've been through.
I would like that.
I'd - I'd even come with you. We can cut our way through the Hells together.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitates a moment, but then commits.

Text.Value: You - do you think it's possible? I suppose there is a chance.
What do you want?
Just when I thought I couldn't love you any more.
Not to mention, I am the Vampire Ascendant. Where else could I find a worthy challenge?
You would?
How I'm free of Cazador. How I have a whole new life stretching out in front of me, and you're-...
That does sound tediously boring. Although, if it's with you... maybe?
Karlach? I asked how are -... No. Not your engine.

EditorData.NodeContext: Rudely asking "Karlach? I asked how are you feeling?" but then realises what's wrong - the engine in her chest is overheating and will kill her.

Text.Value: Although, I couldn't help but notice you said 'we' should find them.

EditorData.NodeContext: a little cautiously

Text.Value: You still have a life to live. Embrace it, my love.
How are you feeling?
I was just thinking about freedom.
Who knows - perhaps we've only just begun.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still processing his love's impending death

Text.Value: The world is ours for the taking. So, what would you like?
True, she could be a threat.

EditorData.NodeContext: Contemplating

Text.Value: Maybe it's better if we're friends for now? You're precious to me and I don't want to lose you, but this is a lot.
And as you're my consort, that makes us the most powerful people in the world.

EditorData.NodeContext: stress on 'us'

Text.Value: I wouldn't subdue the world in Bhaal's name - I'll subdue it in ours.
No. I am beyond your petty power games.
Why stop at two? We could bring this city to its knees.
As much as I want to, I'm not sure if I can.
Good, because selfless as I am, I really did not want to let you go.
I don't think that would be right for either of us.
Let's do this. Together.
Very well. If that's what you want.
I suppose you're right. We've been through enough.
And all it cost was my life in the sun. Now I belong to the shadows.
I think we should break up.
It might be days or years, but he'll come for me eventually. He's inevitable.
How lucky you are that I chose you as my consort. Chose you to help me take Baldur's Gate, then sit by my side as I rule it.
Actually, no. This isn't what I want.
Oh, don't be like that. You can't have thought we'd stay together.
We're not killing our friends, Astarion!
You can't, Astarion. Avernus is a hellscape - literally.
But fine - if you want to make your own future, have at it. And if you crash and burn, that's on your slimy head.
Hahaha! Don't be stupid, darling. You're mine, remember?

EditorData.NodeContext: Genuine laugh - the player can't get away from him. Not even if they want to.

Text.Value: So return to the Hells and do it - live.
So come on, darling. Let's show this world what monsters can do.

EditorData.NodeContext: [Note - this is one of the last lines you can say to the player.]

Text.Value: All right. I'll do it. Back to the Hells - together.
Let's hope they have more sense than that.
Perhaps we'll find somewhere we'd like to stay for a century or two - perhaps not.

Synopsis:
Astarion and the player he's in a romantic relationship with talk in a private bedroom in an inn, the morning after spending the night together after saving the world. A discussion of what comes next ensues, varying depending on how Astarion's story unfolded. He could:
- Have killed Cazador and taken power to become the Vampire Ascendant.
- Have killed Cazador and stayed a spawn (with reactivity to whether or not he killed the Spawn Prisoners.)
- Not killed Cazador.
